{"word":"τραχύστομος","slug":"τραχύστομος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<entryFree id=\"n104642\" key=\"traxu/stomos\" type=\"main\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"entryFree\"> <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">τρᾱχύ-στομος</orth>, <itype lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"itype\">ον</itype>, <sense id=\"n104642.0\" n=\"A\" level=\"1\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">of rough speech</tr_> or <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">pronunciation,</tr_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0099.tlg001.perseus-grc1:14:2:28\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Str.\">Str.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">14.2.28</biblScope></bibl>, where he couples it with <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">παχύστομος,</foreign> and in the same paragraph he writes <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">παχυστομέω </foreign>(<foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">τραχυστομέω</foreign> cod. E, and so it is cited in <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg4083.tlg001:367:29\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Eust.\">Eust.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">367.29</biblScope> </bibl>), <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">παχυστομία.</foreign> </sense> </entryFree>"}]}